🛠️ Standards Compliance
To maintain the quality and reliability of XRD Analyzer Pro Plus, please adhere to the following standards:
Code Style
Language: Python 3.8+
Style Guide: Follow PEP 8 guidelines.
Formatting: Use 4 spaces for indentation.
Naming: Use snake_case for variables/functions and PascalCase for classes.
Documentation
Include docstrings for all new functions and classes.
Update the in-app readme_screen.py "New Features" tab if you add significant functionality.
Update the external README.md if installation steps or dependencies change.
Testing
Include test cases for new parsers in the tests/ directory.
Ensure existing tests pass before submitting a PR.
For algorithmic changes, provide a comparison table (like Table 1 in the manuscript) showing validation against standard data.
Data Privacy & Security
Do not commit sensitive data (e.g., specific laboratory paths, private keys, registry_key.reg).
Do not commit large binary database files (>50MB) directly; use links or instructions to download them separately.
Ensure config.json and settings.ini are excluded via .gitignore if they contain user-specific paths.
💡 Features We Are Looking For
We particularly welcome contributions in the following areas:
New File Format Parsers: Support for additional proprietary formats (e.g., older Siemens, Scintag, or newer Bruker versions).
Database Enhancements: Scripts to convert other open databases (e.g., RRUFF) into our SQLite/JSON format.
Algorithm Improvements: Better background subtraction methods, peak deconvolution, or noise reduction techniques.
Quantitative Analysis: Basic implementation of Reference Intensity Ratio (RIR) methods for semi-quantitative analysis.
UI/UX Improvements: Dark mode support, improved touch gestures, or accessibility enhancements.
Translations: Adding support for languages other than English (e.g., Arabic, French, Spanish) in the GUI.
